lenders.name: Meg Dillion
lenders.loan_because: I would like to help make a difference in the lives of others. This is a new journey for me. I have struggled over where to begin and how I can really make a difference, but I know that little steps can turn into giant leaps.
lenders.occupational_info:
My name is Meg. I am 31 years old and live outside of San Francisco, California in the United States. I was born and raised in a suburb of Chicago, Illinois and I graduated from the University of Iowa. I have also had the opportunity to spend a few years in New York City prior to moving out west.

I've spent the past few months furthering my education, mainly through documentaries and research, on a few pressing issues, which include ending sex trafficking and violence, aiding those in poverty, and empowering women through education and resources.

I am beginning to realize that I have lived a fairly sheltered life. I am not sure whether that is a blessing or a curse. If I had begun helping others sooner, how many more lives could I have positively impacted?

More than anything, I try to see others on a human level. If I can help to positively influence an individual's life, than I will know that I am one step closer to achieving a dream of my own.
